Hi,

The idea isn't really to think about queues (or exchanges), but in terms of the messaging patterns (PUB/SUB, REQUEST/REPLY, etc.). All of those that read from a socket have the messages buffered in a queue.

If you're trying to interoperate with AMQP clients, though, it helps to know that PUSH sockets and REQ sockets both publish to the queue that they are connected to. E.g., in

```
$ var push = context.socket('PUSH');
$ push.connect('foobar');
$ push.write("here is some stuff", 'utf8');
```

the message gets sent to a shared queue called 'foobar'.

